			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1455337">
									

<p>I'm sorry for the necopost, but I just wanted to say that this reference flipped my vote. I had thought magma was dangerous enough before, but this would've been ridiculous. Upvoted, but I have one minor nitpick/pet peeve.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-788 was discovered following the 19██ <strong>eruption of [REDACTED]</strong>. It is currently theorized that multiple instances of SCP-788 may exist in the mantle layer of the earth, and the <strong>eruption of [REDACTED]</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p>The fact that there's repetition without literary reason was jarring, especially considering how they're directly atop one another (at least in my view). Replacement of the second &quot;eruption of [REDACTED]&quot; with &quot;the aforementioned volcanic disturbance&quot; or something similar would easily fix this little snag.</p>
<p>(If for whatever reason that this kind of necropost is still against etiquette, then drop me a PM and I'll delete it and know better for the future.)</p>

